# Swagger Documentation

This project uses [swaggo/swag](https://github.com/swaggo/swag). Generated files live in `docs/`:

- `docs/docs.go`
- `docs/swagger.json`
- `docs/swagger.yaml`

## When to Regenerate

After any change that affects the public HTTP API, regenerate Swagger in the same task:

- new/changed routes in `transport/http/routes.go`
- new/changed handlers in `transport/http/handler.go`
- new/changed request/response types in `transport/http/responses.go` or handler request structs
- new/changed `@Summary`, `@Router`, `@Param`, `@Success`, `@Failure` godoc annotations

## How to Annotate

Add swag godoc comments above handler methods:

```go
// UpdateBalance godoc
// @Summary Update Beeline balance
// @Tags beeline config
// @Accept json
// @Produce json
// @Param input body UpdateBalanceRequest true "Balance update payload"
// @Success 200 {object} ConfigResponse
// @Failure 400 {object} BeelineErrorResponse
// @Router /banks/beeline/config/balance [patch]
func (h *Handler) UpdateBalance(c *gin.Context) {
```

Put reusable DTOs in `transport/http/responses.go` when possible so swag can reference them in `{object}` tags.

## Regenerate Command

Run from repo root after API changes:

```bash
go run github.com/swaggo/swag/cmd/swag@v1.16.6 init -g cmd/api/main.go -o docs --parseDependency --parseInternal
```

Do not hand-edit generated files in `docs/docs.go`, `docs/swagger.json`, or `docs/swagger.yaml`.

## Checklist

1. Add or update godoc annotations on handlers
2. Add or update response/request structs with `json` tags
3. Run the swag command above
4. Verify `/swagger/index.html` shows the new or updated endpoint
